The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Anand plans secret weapon

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Viswanathan Anand is planning to use a secret weapon in his bid to regain the world chess championship. 

I have a secret weapon for the championship but cannot reveal it as I dont want it to be publicised, worlds No. 1 chess player said at a city hotel on Friday. 

Anands revelation came a day after announcing that he wanted to regain the world title as No. 1 player. He had won it in 2000. 

According to Anand, there is a good demand of chess players for the sponsors. If you can promote the game well, sponsors are bound to come, he said. 

Anand played a rapid simultaneous chess with 30 students from various engineering colleges of the state. 

Among them, Ushashi Chakraborty of Future Institute of Engineering and Management impressed Anand most. 

Anand left the city on Friday evening. 




